{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:second-timothy.2",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Timothy 2 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:1",
      "text": "You therefore, my child, be strengthened in the grace that is in Christ Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:2",
      "text": "The things which you have heard from me among many witnesses, commit the same things to faithful men who will be able to teach others also.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:3",
      "text": "You therefore must endure hardship as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:4",
      "text": "No soldier on duty entangles himself in the affairs of life, that he may please him who enrolled him as a soldier.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:5",
      "text": "Also, if anyone competes in athletics, he isn’t crowned unless he has competed by the rules.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:6",
      "text": "The farmer who labors must be the first to get a share of the crops.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:7",
      "text": "Consider what I say, and may the Lord give you understanding in all things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:8",
      "text": "Remember Jesus Christ, risen from the dead, of the offspring of David, according to my Good News,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:9",
      "text": "in which I suffer hardship to the point of chains as a criminal. But God’s word isn’t chained.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:10",
      "text": "Therefore I endure all things for the chosen ones’ sake, that they also may obtain the salvation which is in Christ Jesus with eternal glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:11",
      "text": "This saying is trustworthy: “For if we died with him, we will also live with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:12",
      "text": "If we endure, we will also reign with him. If we deny him, he also will deny us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:13",
      "text": "If we are faithless, he remains faithful; for he can’t deny himself.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:14",
      "text": "Remind them of these things, charging them in the sight of the Lord that they don’t argue about words to no profit, to the subverting of those who hear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:15",
      "text": "Give diligence to present yourself approved by God, a workman who doesn’t need to be ashamed, properly handling the Word of Truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:16",
      "text": "But shun empty chatter, for it will go further in ungodliness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:17",
      "text": "and those words will consume like gangrene, of whom is Hymenaeus and Philetus:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:18",
      "text": "men who have erred concerning the truth, saying that the resurrection is already past, and overthrowing the faith of some.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:19",
      "text": "However, God’s firm foundation stands, having this seal: “The Lord knows those who are his,” and, “Let every one who names the name of the Lord depart from unrighteousness.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:20",
      "text": "Now in a large house there are not only vessels of gold and of silver, but also of wood and of clay. Some are for honor and some for dishonor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:21",
      "text": "If anyone therefore purges himself from these, he will be a vessel for honor, sanctified, and suitable for the master’s use, prepared for every good work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:22",
      "text": "Flee from youthful lusts; but pursue righteousness, faith, love, and peace with those who call on the Lord out of a pure heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:23",
      "text": "But refuse foolish and ignorant questionings, knowing that they generate strife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:24",
      "text": "The Lord’s servant must not quarrel, but be gentle toward all, able to teach, patient,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:25",
      "text": "in gentleness correcting those who oppose him. Perhaps God may give them repentance leading to a full knowledge of the truth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-timothy.2.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:26",
      "text": "and they may recover themselves out of the devil’s snare, having been taken captive by him to do his will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
